  "body": "## Summary\n- Add a local Quartz Hypothesis component/plugin that injects the official browser embed only when `HYPOTHESIS_ENABLED=true`.\n- Support build-time options for sidebar state, highlights, comments mode, group allowlist, and theme.\n- Pass Hypothesis repository variables into the site validation build and document setup in the README.\n- Keep agent-facing Hypothesis API access out of this PR; that should be handled separately as a Sepo runtime capability.\n\n## Verification\n- `npm run check`\n- `npm run build`\n- `HYPOTHESIS_ENABLED=true HYPOTHESIS_OPEN_SIDEBAR=true HYPOTHESIS_COMMENTS_MODE=true HYPOTHESIS_GROUPS_ALLOWLIST=abc123,def456 HYPOTHESIS_THEME=clean npm run quartz -- build`\n- Confirmed disabled output has no Hypothesis embed/config and enabled output includes the embed loader/config.\n\nRefs: https://h.readthedocs.io/projects/client/en/latest/publishers/embedding.html, https://h.readthedocs.io/projects/client/en/latest/publishers/config.html\n\nCloses #8\n",
